trnCpqAdapterTable.name: trnCpqAdapterTable
trnCpqAdapterTable.description: This table contains the configuration and status information for the Token Ring 4/16 adapter cards.

trnCpqAdapterOpenInWrapMode.name: trnCpqAdapterOpenInWrapMode
trnCpqAdapterOpenInWrapMode.description: This enables the adapter to open in Wrap Mode. In order to set/reset this parameter, close the logical port, change the value and open the port.

trnCpqMtu.name: trnCpqMtu
trnCpqMtu.description: This specifies the mtu for the adapter. The actual packet size may be less depending on other adapters in the unit. Changes will not take affect until the next reboot.

trnCpqNoOfLinkResets.name: trnCpqNoOfLinkResets
trnCpqNoOfLinkResets.description: This object is a count of the number of resets which have occurred on this Token Ring link, since the last reinitialization of the unit.

trnCpqLastLinkResetReason.name: trnCpqLastLinkResetReason
trnCpqLastLinkResetReason.description: This object gives the a reason code for the last reset which occurred on this Token ring port. This object gives the reason code for the last reset which occurred on this LAN physical link. A value of noReason(1) is returned if the link has not reset. A value of management(2) is returned when a link reset has been caused by SNMP. A value of deviceError(3) is returned if the link reset was caused by a hardware failure.

trnCpqTimeSinceLastLinkReset.name: trnCpqTimeSinceLastLinkReset
trnCpqTimeSinceLastLinkReset.description: This object gives the time (in hundreths of seconds) since the last link reset, eg. The time since the last link went down. The value of this object is zero if no link resets have occured since the last reinitialization of the unit.
